        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "The door companies would price all doors from 1x1 to 15x10 as a 15x10 door. All Doors from 1x10.125 to 15x20 as 15x20 door."
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "At this point a 14 x 18 Door would be Size F, a 30 x 36 Door would be size S."
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "The next step in the Door Matrix pricing setup is to set prices for A, B, C etc."
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "The Door Material would determine a different set of prices even though the sizes were fixed. In other words Size F might be $34 dollars for Ash and Oak and $47 dollars for Maple. You would setup two prices for this Matrix, one called Ash/Oak the other called Premium (anything descriptive)."
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "You can setup as many different Size Matrices as needed for the different Door manufacturers then can set pricing in the Size Matrices as needed."
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "At the Door Material tab you can then select a Matrix price for the Door (Ash/Oak)."
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "Although users using a Price Matrix, typically, only price with the Matrixany other Door pricing you have setup will be added to the Matrix Price. In other words if your size F for a Oak door is $34 the final price for the Door will be more if you have a $/door or $/SqFt for the Door, Materials or Profiles."
        }
    ],
